B® Missing the Boat and Remaining Upside: The most common investor questions on KL mark lanes@credit-suisse.com

are regarding the amount of upside left, given the stock’s strong performance to date, and

whether investors who have not already bought KL have missed the story. We continue to

see upside, albeit more limited than the recent trend, from Fostervile and Macassa

exploration, but the valuation gives us pause, as it seems to price in continued jumps in

reserves. We believe that even a single weaker reserve/exploration update at Fosterville

and/or Macassa that curbs the positive grade trend could see the stock pull back. m Lack of Near-Term Catalysts Beyond Exploration Updates: While the ramp-up of

enough to move the stock higher. In addition, completion of Shaft #4 at Macassa, which

adds significant production, will not be completed until 2022. ®m Valuation: Our US$47 TP is based on a 50/50 blended valuation of NAV and FY20
